    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n5249" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">κέραμος</span></b> : anything of
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">earthen</span> ware, <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">pot</span> or
            <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">jar</span>, such as are sometimes found half buried in the
          earth (see cut), <i><span class="en">Il. 3.469</span></i>; in <i><span class="en">Il. 5.387</span></i>, <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">χαλκέῳ ἐν
            κεράμῳ</span>, serving as a dungeon (cf. the pit into which
          Joseph was thrown by his brethren). 
        </div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
